                        <interp inst="t18551022-name-180" type="surname" value="ADLINGTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18551022-name-180" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES ADLINGTON</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. This letter marked "A" is my writing—(<hi rend="italic">read</hi>: "Gravesend, 3rd Sept., 1855. Gentlemen, I in close you a cheque for 46<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 14<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., which please place to my credit; I have not sent the cash for the lard, &amp;c.,")</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">The prisoner's statement before the Magistrate wag read as follows</hi>:—I know nothing of the cheque; I picked up the two letters and one envelope all wrapped up, and put them in my pocket; as for the other letters that I detained, I was afraid to deliver them.")</p>
